**Why two different pictures of enrollment can both be true:** the 85,000 figure is *gross terminations during open enrollment*; the −2% figure is the *net* change once new sign-ups are counted; the 120,000+ and 160,000+ figures are *cumulative*, adding in people who dropped coverage after open enrollment closed (commonly for nonpayment once the higher bill arrived). If you see a single number reported as "the" 2026 enrollment change, ask which of these three it's measuring.

**GLP-1 drug pricing:** A federal agreement with GLP-1 manufacturers (branded in reporting as "TrumpRx"), reached in late 2025, reportedly caps Medicare beneficiaries' out-of-pocket cost at $50/month for GLP-1 agonists, with Medicare Part D coverage beginning July 2026; cash-pay price targets for non-Medicare patients are reported around $350/month. *(Moderate confidence — sourced to the background compilation, not independently re-verified this session; if this matters to a specific decision, confirm current terms directly with your plan or Medicare.gov.)* Pennsylvania Medicaid ended adult weight-loss coverage for these drugs effective January 1, 2026.

