## 4. Ghost Networks: What the Law Actually Lets You Do

A 2026 state-commissioned "secret shopper" audit reportedly found that a large share of provider directory listings in Pennsylvania ACA plans contained at least one inaccuracy, and that behavioral health listings were the worst offenders — only a small fraction of listed mental health providers could actually schedule a new-patient appointment when contacted. *(Moderate confidence; this figure comes from the background compilation and was not independently re-verified against the original study this session — if you're citing this in a formal complaint, ask the Pennsylvania Insurance Department for the underlying audit.)*

**If an inaccurate directory sends you to a doctor who turns out to be out-of-network, here is what actually protects you — not what a chatbot summary said protects you:**

| Situation | Your actual protection | Who enforces it |
|---|---|---|
| Provider directory was wrong; you didn't know they were out-of-network | 28 Pa. Code § 9.725 (hold-harmless): you generally owe only your in-network cost-sharing | Pennsylvania Insurance Department |
| Provider didn't tell you they were out-of-network before a non-emergency visit | Act 252 of 2023 (point-of-service disclosure): the balance bill is presumed illegal | Pennsylvania Insurance Department / Attorney General |
| Your plan's directory doesn't reflect real provider availability | 42 U.S.C. § 300gg-115 (federal directory-accuracy requirement) | Pennsylvania Insurance Department / HHS |
| A payment *amount* dispute between your out-of-network emergency or ancillary provider and your insurer | Federal IDR (45 C.F.R. § 149.510) — **but this is between the provider and the plan, not something you personally file** | The provider or the plan initiates it |

**What to actually do:** If you get an unexpected out-of-network bill, don't call it "surprise billing" and stop there — cite 28 Pa. Code § 9.725 and Act 252 by name in writing to your insurer, and file a complaint with the PID if they don't fix it (contact info below).

