## 6. If You're Denied a Claim or a Medication

**Act 146 (Prior Authorization and External Review)** gives you the right to an independent external review of a denial, with a 45-day maximum turnaround, and reported reversal rates around 42% (Moderate confidence, compilation-sourced). This is one of the strongest tools an individual enrollee has — use it before assuming a denial is final, especially for GLP-1 or other specialty-drug denials.

Typical GLP-1 prior-authorization criteria reported for 2026 plans include a BMI of 30+ (or 27+ with a comorbidity such as hypertension or sleep apnea), documented failure of at least two lower-tier weight-management drugs, and ongoing proof of a supervised weight-management program. *(Moderate confidence — verify your specific plan's criteria in your Evidence of Coverage, since these vary by carrier.)*

